criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Non small cell lung cancer patients confirmed by pathology;

          2. They were 18-80 years old;

          3. The tumor could not be resected or could not tolerate surgery;

          4. Planed to receive chemoradiotherapy and subsequent immunoconsolidation therapy;

          5. Clinical stage III (AJCC, 8th Edition, 2017);

          6. After systematic detection of non-small cell lung cancer core indicators including
             EGFR, ALK, ros1, KRAS, ntrk, TMB, etc;

          7. Patient informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. After radiotherapy and chemotherapy, the disease progressed and immune maintenance
             therapy could not be carried out

          2. It can not cooperate with the completion of baseline mutation screening and subsequent
             sample detection

          3. Factors judged by other researchers not suitable for further study
